    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-07T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-07T22:00:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.8836/872: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-07T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 7, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>606. Refer your 617, July 28. War Production Board advise that upon application
                    they will grant exemptions from M–63<note n="44" xml:id="d378fn44">General
                        Imports Order M–63; 6 <hi rend="italic">Federal Register</hi> 6796.</note>
                    to import Isle of Pines grapefruit. It is expected that grapefruit will be
                    removed from the M–63 List when next amendment is printed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
